!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

thermal /ˈθɜːməl/

(thermals) 

1. ADJ Thermal means relating to or caused by heat or by changes in temperature. 热的; 由热引起的; 由温度变化引起的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...thermal power stations. …热电站。 

2. ADJ Thermal streams or baths contain water which is naturally hot or warm. 天然温热的 [ADJ n] 

例： Volcanic activity has created thermal springs and boiling mud pools. 火山活动产生了温泉和沸腾的泥浆池。 

3. ADJ Thermal clothes are specially designed to keep you warm in cold weather. 保暖的 (衣服) [ADJ n] 

例： ...thermal underwear. …保暖内衣 

例： My feet were like blocks of ice despite the thermal socks. 我的双脚尽管穿着保暖袜，还是像冰块。 

4. N-PLURAL Thermals are thermal clothes. 保暖衣 

例： Have you got your thermals on? 你穿上保暖衣了吗？ 

5. N-COUNT A thermal is a movement of rising warm air. 上升的暖气流 

例： Birds use thermals to lift them through the air. 鸟类利用上升的暖气流升空。

</div>

